metadata.description:
I wrote "Head Above" at my piano on a rainy LA day. 

It’s gone through many revisions (one that even dropped on LNRZ with Bloody White and Clear Eyes). The final version is releasing on DSPs on Jan 27th and it features Reo Cragun. 

Hope you listen and feel like the main character of your own action film.

Talking myself back in
Say the right words
Or leave it all in my head
To sing like a curse

I never made it out
I never trust myself
I can see a lot between the mirror
I can see a lot between my eyes

[Chorus]
I’m so full of it
I lost myself
But I’m keeping my head above
But I’m keeping my head above

I’m so full of it
It’s all I know
But I’m keeping my head above
But I’m keeping my head above

Head above

I took five shots of the liquor
I love how it numb my feelings

I’m doing seven figure deals, how you feel bout that?
